Package dog.giraffe.util

Common abstractions and helper methods.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Block
    An executable block of code.
    Consumer<T>
    An operation that accepts values.
    Function<T,​U>
    A generic function, a mapping between objects.
    QuickSort.Compare
    Represents the comparability of the elements of a list-like object.
    QuickSort.Swap
    Represents the ability to swap two elements of a list-like object.
    Supplier<T>
    An operation that returns a value.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ColorConverter
    RGB<->HSV/HSL color conversion.
    Doubles
    Collection of helper methods operating on doubles.
    LexicographicComparator<T>
    Abstract description of a lexicographic order for list-like objects.
    Lists
    Collection of helper methods operating on Lists.
    Pair<T,​U>
    Immutable container of two values.
    QuickSort
    Implementation of Hoare's selection algorithm to select the median of a list-like collection of values.
